			<a class='comment-reply-link' href='/2011/05/tiger-woods-the-modern-day-mickey-mantle/?replytocom=30132#respond' onclick='return addComment.moveForm("comment-30132", "30132", "respond", "30823")'>Reply</a>		</div>

		<ul class='children'>

	<li class="comment byuser comment-author-jerod bypostauthor even depth-2" id="comment-30133">

		
		<div class="comment-header">
			<div class="comment-author vcard">
				<img alt='' src='http://0.gravatar.com/avatar/210956d889a29b6284564ba98ebc6686?s=48&amp;d=http%3A%2F%2F0.gravatar.com%2Favatar%2Fad516503a11cd5ca435acc9bb6523536%3Fs%3D48&amp;r=PG' class='avatar avatar-48 photo' height='48' width='48' />				<cite class="fn"><a href='http://www.midwestsportsfans.com' rel='external nofollow' class='url'>JerodMSF</a></cite> <span class="says">says:</span>		 	</div><!-- end .comment-author -->

			<div class="comment-meta commentmetadata">
				<a href="http://www.midwestsportsfans.com/2011/05/tiger-woods-the-modern-day-mickey-mantle/#comment-30133">May 16, 2011 at 7:45 am</a>
							</div><!-- end .comment-meta -->
		</div>

		<div class="comment-content">
			
			<p>Agree that this is a difference between them. From what I&#039;ve read and been told, since I wasn&#039;t alive then, Mantle dealt with his injuries gracefully and with team-first toughness. The difference here is that Woods is his own one-man team, and it is very hard for any of us to know what his specific injuries are like, but certainly the PERCEPTION of how he is dealing with his injuries differs from the perception of how Mantle did.  </p>
		</div><!-- end .comment-content -->

